
Overview of verb shorten

The verb shorten has 5 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (6) shorten -- (make shorter than originally intended; reduce or retrench in length or duration; "He shortened his trip due to illness")
2. (3) abridge, foreshorten, abbreviate, shorten, cut, contract, reduce -- (reduce in scope while retaining essential elements; "The manuscript must be shortened")
3. shorten -- (make short or shorter; "shorten the skirt"; "shorten the rope by a few inches")
4. shorten -- (become short or shorter; "In winter, the days shorten")
5. bowdlerize, bowdlerise, expurgate, castrate, shorten -- (edit by omitting or modifying parts considered indelicate; "bowdlerize a novel")
